Retained earnings represent the cumulative net income (or loss) of a company after accounting for dividends. In this case, we'll assume there are no dividends, so the retained earnings at the end of the period will be the initial retained earnings plus the net income (or minus the net loss) for the period.

### Step 1: Determine Initial Retained Earnings
From the problem, there is no initial retained earnings mentioned, so we'll assume it starts at 0.
